## Conversation
Same session as the Fable 5 settings bump (0f67285). After switching all
models to Fable 5, the user asked: "let's go through the entire set of rules,
prompts, skills and there's a new Fable 5 prompting guide
(https://platform.claude.com/docs/en/build-with-claude/prompt-engineering/prompting-claude-fable-5)
and I want to re-write all prompts and skills, etc with the fable 5 prompting
guide". This is the rules/ half; the abatilo-core plugin half is the next
commit. Direct successor to 60d6907, which did the same retune for Opus 4.8.

## Actions
- Downloaded the raw guide via curl (the .md suffix on platform.claude.com
  URLs returns raw markdown) to /tmp/fable5-guide.md; 223 lines
- Ran a Workflow (run wf_4463b028-e85, 26 agents, ~926k subagent tokens):
  per-file rewrite agent -> fresh-context adversarial verifier -> fixer
  stage. All 13 verdicts came back approve with zero fix rounds
- Rules scope: task-tracking, commit-notes, simple, subtractive-engineering
  changed; codex-mcp and CLAUDE_global verified already-aligned, no edits
- Key deletions (each justified as compensation for a prior-model weakness):
  task-tracking's "You LOVE making task lists"/"EVERYTHING"/zero-bar persona
  hyperbole and the per-completion TaskList re-poll; commit-notes' triple
  restatement of "always add notes"; simple.md's duplicate Codex Behavior
  line; subtractive-engineering's 3 redundant gate restatements
- Orchestrator (me) reviewed every diff in full before committing

## Errors & Mistakes
One workflow-script wart: the FILES array initially had a malformed
placeholder path for repo-explore ("skills/task: repo-explore/SKILL.md")
patched immediately after the literal via FILES[6] = {...}. Worked correctly
but is ugly; a clean literal would have been better.

## Dead Ends
None. Considered de-capping the "CONSULT Codex" token in simple.md; kept it
because it is the file's defined term and subtractive-engineering.md
cross-references it verbatim — lowercasing requires a coordinated two-file
change with no clear benefit.

## Hints for Future Agents
- The Fable 5 guide's core lesson for these files: brief plain instructions
  beat enumeration; PREFER DELETING an instruction that compensated for an
  old model's weakness over rewording it; never bake model-version notes
  ("Opus 4.8 under-delegates") into prompt artifacts — that is exactly how
  60d6907's now-stale notes accumulated.
- Flagged judgment calls if behavior regresses: (1) task-tracking's new
  threshold is "multiple distinct steps, files, or decisions" — loosen if
  Aaron wants tasks on small two-step fixes; (2) the "Check TaskList after
  completing each task" deletion assumes status updates suffice — restore if
  tasks start going stale mid-session.
- The WHEN/DO/PREFER/AVOID keyword convention in simple.md is structure (a
  consistent DSL), not emphasis inflation. Leave it.
- Reasoning-echo audit (Fable 5 refuses reasoning-extraction prompts): all
  rules files are clean. commit-notes documents the session record (actions,
  errors, dead ends), which is NOT reasoning transcription — keep it that way
  when editing.

## Codebase Discoveries
- CLAUDE_global.md (the 4 communication bullets) already matches the Fable 5
